Example
Test a second condition if the first condition is not met:
<?php
if(5 < 3) {
echo "Five is less than three";
} else 
  if(5 > 4) {
echo "Five is greater than four";
}
?>

Definition and Usage
The
elseif
keyword tests a new condition if the condition of a 
if
or
elseif
statement was not met. It is equivalent to putting an
if
statement inside an else block.
The following blocks of code are equivalent:
<?php
if (...) {
some code here
} elseif (...) {
some 
  code here
}
?>
<?php
if (...) {
some code here
} else{
if (...) 
  {
some code here
}
}
?>
